@node about " Fucking Fast Login v1.4 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@prev main
@{"°°" link grems}
   _____  _              _
  /  _  \| |__  ___ _  _| |_
 |   _   | '_ \/ _ \ || |  _|
 |__| |__|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Fucking Fast Login (aka: FFL) is another great MAXs door that  allows the
 Almighty SysOp and selected Users (via "FFL.users" listing) to bypass all
 the doors executed  during the "Intro/Maindoor.text" login sequence.  The
 mail checking is not skipped.

 Fucking (..Oops, that bad word again) Fast Login  simply makes logging in
 much quicker and is great for the SysOp when he(she) logs onto the BBS.

 FFL 1.4 is a tiny update from v1.2 ('97). Don't like it, don't use it! :)

@endnode
@node run " Fucking Fast Login v1.4 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also, you crazy SysOp.

 Move the "FFL" directory into  the "gremlins" dir and run  the door (FFL)
 via the "Introdoor.text" (see example) sequence, as your very first door.
 Run the second door (FFL_2) as the last door in your "Maindoor.text" (see
 example).

 Create a directory  called "intro" in the doors dir.  This dir (intro) is
 renamed to "intro_ffl" when FFL  is first run and renamed back when FFL_2
 is run. All doors (the executables only) are placed in this "intro"  dir,
 as well as remaining in their normal dir's or paths, if you need 'em.

 For each door run via "Intro/Maindoor.text" you must alter it's  path and
 have each door (the executable) run from the new path if you want  FFL to
 skip them. See "Intro/Maindoor.text" for self explanation.

 Example: intro/wall

 In brief, when FFL is run, it  renames the dir to "intro_ffl" and each of
 the doors are not located because the path name has changed, thus each of
 the doors in "intro" path are skipped. ..Understand? ;)

 For FFL axs to Users, place thier name in the "FFL.users" file (see eg.).
 The "FFL.menu" can be altered if you desire, but why bother, it's cool?!

 Last thing, place the following lines in your logoff script as this  will
 ensure that if the "intro"  dir has been renamed to "intro_ffl",  that it
 is indeed changed back (incase FFL_2 missed it?):

  if exists doors:intro_ffl
  rename doors:intro_ffl doors:intro
  endif

 And that should be about it, hopefully..!? ;-)

 Need help, further info or something, then @{"contact" link call} me.

@endnode
