@node hist " Fucking Fast Login v1.4 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  __   __ _    _
 |  |_|  (_)__| |_ ___ _ _ _  _
 |   _   | (_-<  _/ _ \ '_| || |
 |__| |__|_/__/\__\___/_|  \_, | @{b}of Glen Martin@{ub}
                           |__/

    It all started when my mate  gave me a box, a slow 2400 modem in 1994.
 I plugged it into my computer and  this was my  first experience with the
 modem and BBS world.  I soon logged onto a few BBS's, and got to know how
 it all worked.  One SysOp showed me his BBS and explained it all to me in
 more detail.  I became involved, and wanted my own BBS.

    Late 1994 or so, I started  my own small  BBS using MAXs BBS 1.54  and
 this was my first encounter with MAXs.  I then moved  around and  the BBS
 went  with me.  I then thought about programming and another SysOp got me
 started and helped me out.  Before I knew it, I was programming a heap of
 doors for the great MAXs BBS,  first door evolving in 1995 and  many more
 doors created since then, right up till now.  I still program today!

    I'm dedicated to MAXs and everything I create is dedicated to MAXs BBS
 and every MAXs SysOp (..and Fluffy Net).  If anybody wants to start a BBS
 using MAXs, as I have helped many SysOp's before or need help (anything),
 then contact me and I'll be more than happy to assist you in anyway.  And
 if you don't like it, then don't use it.

    Hello and thanks to all those around the world who have emailed me! As
 long as Gremlins BBS is still online, I'll still be around for a while?!

    Regards,
